Heat oven to 350 degrees F. Chop Simply Potatoes(R) into small pieces. Place in microwaveable bowl; add water. Cover, microwave on HIGH 3 to 4 minutes or until potatoes are tender; drain water. In medium bowl stir together cooked potatoes, ham, cheese, sour cream and cumin; mix well. Remove biscuits from package; carefully separate each in half. Press each biscuit into a 3 1/2 -inch circle. Spoon a generous 1 tablespoon potato mixture in center of each biscuit. Fold biscuit over filling creating a half moon shape; press edges to seal. Place puffs on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown. Best if served warm.